pageTitle: Daimler AG : Bahrain Grand Prix: Race | 4-Traders
textBeforeTable: The team averaged 22.216 seconds in the pit lane over six pit stops, with Michael the day's fastest three-stopper Michael made three stops on laps 9, 23 and 37, also running an option/option/prime/prime strategy Starting from P22, Michael climbed 12 positions through the field over the course of the race to finish in P10 He completed three stops on laps 8, 22 and 36 running an option/option/prime/prime tyre strategy Nico had a hard-fought race, running in P9 through the opening stint, then gaining places as the race unfolded Nico Rosberg and Michael Schumacher both scored points in the Bahrain Grand Prix today as the MERCEDES AMG PETRONAS pair finished the 57-lap race in fifth and tenth places respectively. *Required fields Message : (You can enter multiple email addresses separated by commas) To* : From* : Name : Last Name : Send by mail:
